n to despair that this trip would show precious little side profit, but onward through Kithicor I travelled.<br><br>After a time, the trees parted, and the gently sloping commonlands stretched out before me.  I paced myself carefully, and made good time, skirting the orc camps, but pausing to spy upon the new Teir'Dal shelters that seem to dot these hills.  This is something I think will need investigation, but for now my objective lay far to the south.  As I crossed the plains, I came upon a druid who had made camp on the plain, and was resting from his wounds.  Such magics as they possess are useful in far travels, and it was worth my time to speak amiably with him, for he imbued me with the spirit of wolf before we parted ways.<br><br>From there, the miles fairly flew.  The rest of the commonlands and northern Ro were a blur.  I paused for nothing to make the most of the enchantment upon me, and it wasn't until I was well south of the Oasis that next I stopped.  I had to, for the scene below me was startling.  Just over the rise, the largest spider I have ever seen, was doing battle with a Teir'Dal magician and his elemental.  I have seen the elementals of our master magisters, they are enormous and this one was called by the most powerful magics for certain.<br><br>There is a subtle beauty to spiders, and I confess I was torn in who I wished to see prevail.  Carelessly, I moved closer to the battle, and the spider {who I am told is a rare breed called the terrorantula}, grazed me while thrashing about, and that one scratch from his razor fangs poisoned me.  I threw myself back out of harms way and immeadiately began tending the wound.  It was difficult.  I felt like my entire arm was on fire.  I've sampled many poisons in my rogue studies, and I think this is what saved me.  Sprawled half dead in the sands, my body was finally able to fight off the poison.  When I finally staggered to my feet, the mage was gone, and only the giant carcass of the terrorantula remained.<br><br>Searching the body, I found several strands of terrorantula silk left behind by the mage, and carefully preserved them in my pack.  Profit at last, but the cost was nearly too high.  I recentered myself by the unyielding and punishing light of the sun, and set off south again, leaving the desert and entering the hills that separate it from the swamps of Innothule.<br><br>to be continued,<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://andais.homestead.com/files/andais.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uandais.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Andais</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#B30000>(7/23/01 2:21:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The search for Gazunga</span><hr size=1> Innothule swamp was every bit as fetid and slimy as the legends implied.  I did everything possible to stay on the outer edge of the mire, but at times the slopes crumbled beneath me, and I found myself knee deep in bog.  Thank Innoruuk that ravenscale doesn't rust.  Eventually, the ground beneath me grew firmer, and I was able to leave that unpleasant place behind.  I hoped the journey would be worth it, and I would find some news of our Gazunga.<br><br>The Feerott is known as the playground of ogre-kind.  I walked carefully in this place, for the Spirit of Wolf was fading, and in Neriak it is understood that the ogres don't always remember their friends when their stomachs are growling.  I have confidence in my combat training from the Hall of the Ebon Mask, but I also know that to the denizens of Oggok, I may appear only as a tender morsel of flesh.  When Oggok came into sight, I was much relieved, for though they eyed a stranger like myself apprehensively, they seemed willing to talk.<br><br>I wandered their city for awhile and spoke first with the merchants.  They are generally willing to add some information to the scale to balance a generous measure of gold.  Though few could claim to be familiar with Gazunga, his reputation as a warrior was fairly common.  Two merchants in particular seemed to know him, an ogre Chef that claimed he used to buy supplies from her regularly, and a bartender {I believe his name was Clurg} that said he'd been in to drink from time to time.  Neither had seen him in recent memory however.<br><br>I then approached some of the city guard, who the ogres call bouncers.  Like many guards, they seemed hesitant to speak with me, other than to occasionally confirm that Gazunga hadn't been about but there had been some whispers of him being seen near the temple of Cazic Thule.  There seemed little choice but to follow the trail the rumors had blazed.<br><br>It was a fair distance from the ogre town to the temple.  {Which speaks well of the lizardmen's guile, I wouldn't make camp too near a city of idle ogres either}  There was a makeshift bridge across the river in the form of a fallen obelisk, but I chose to swim the alligator infested span in the hopes that I could gain access to the temple unseen.  My skills sustained me and soon I stood at the enterance.<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://andais.homestead.com/files/gazseek1.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>The lizards were not as large as I had expected them to be, but regardless I approached unseen, and moved into the tunnel that led to the inner courtyard.  It was disturbing to see the litter of bodies that filled that hall.  Adventurers that apparently never got far enough to again see the skies of the feerott.  It was reassuring that none of the bodies were Teir'Dal.<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://andais.homestead.com/files/gazseek2.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>I crept down the corridor, stepping over the carcasses of the fallen, and slipped past the sentries into the courtyard of the temple.  The minions of Cazic Thule, and perhaps news of our companion lay just beyond.<br><br>to be continued, <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ulorellai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lorellai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#B30000>(7/24/01 8:59:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The search for Gazunga</span><hr size=1> Lorellai concentrates, focusing on the bond of her guild, and the journals of her guildmates appear before her eyes.   She reads with intensity,  following the threads of her mates with heart racing, hoping for their safety.  with trembling hand she adds her own entry:<br><br>Andais,<br>     You are indeed and accomplished rogue.  Be safe on your jouneys.  I am hoping to find Gazunga soon.  I may have cause to celebrate a wedding in the near future, and it is important to me that Gazunga is there.  I will send out a bird to deliver a message. With strong magic the message will get through, but unless he replies I will never know if the message reached him.  Keep searching.  And again, be safe.<br><br>Lorellai<br>Bard 22nd song <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uandais.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Andais</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#B30000>(7/25/01 3:42:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The search for Gazunga</span><hr size=1> The lizards of Cazic Thule, were hardly the semi-mindless brutes I expected.  They have surprised me several times now.  Their shaman caste draws remarkable healing spells from the Faceless One, and on more than one occasion it was a near thing to decide if my toxins would slay my opponent before he could draw enough breath to petition his god's magic.  My rogue skills served me well in isolating stragglers in the enormous maze just off the courtyard, and in hiding me when I needed time to bind my own wounds.<br><br>Many lizards were questioned at rapier point.  Many were slain for their refusal to speak, but sadly even the ones whose courage failed them could shed no light on the whereabouts of Gazunga.  I even sought so far as to scout out the temple itself.  I hoped to overhear some clue, or boastful tale that might tell me if our ogre were indeed prisioner though I began to despair that such was not the case.<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://andais.homestead.com/files/gazseek3.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>My spying came to naught, and I felt that surely if Gazunga was here, there must be talk of it.  I knew my skills could not keep my actions unnoticed long in the temple, where one grunt of pain or outraged hiss could give me away, and so I retreated again to the courtyard to think.  It was then that the Prince of Hate showed me a small sign of favor.  A lizardman of some importance, travelled from the enterance on towards the maze.  The other lizards showed him some deference, and called him &quot;Radiant&quot;.  <br><br>This creature, I thought, might be more informed than a common sentinel.  My interest was his doom.  Luring him to a quiet corner of the courtyard, my blades &amp; toxins did their work, and soon Radiant lay at my feet.  I questioned him before his end, but he swore he knew nothing of Gazunga.  Only one truly ignorant or intensely strong could have withstood the questioning of one of the Ebon Mask, and so I must accept that our ogre is not in the hands of the lizardmen of the Temple of Cazic-Thule.<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://andais.homestead.com/files/gazseek4.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>After returning to Oggok to resupply, I heard of some of the rumors that put him near Qeynos.  That place welcomes me only dubiously if at all, and so I leave it to my fellow Draconians to investigate the civilized lands.  Perhaps in time, one of us will find him.<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://andais.homestead.com/files/andais.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> A voice in the back of your mind</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#B30000>(8/5/01 9:24:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> He is mine.</span><hr size=1> Your search is in vain, you insects.  Unless you are eager to leave this mortal plane, you will cease this bothersome search at once. Defy my orders, and you will pay dearly...<br><br>Gazunga means nothing to you... he is just a puppet. A pawn to be pushed around by those around him. And he is MY puppet now, my new face. He runs around, like a scared little rodent, obeying my slightest whim...<br><br>Do you wish to take him back? To take him from my hands, and use him for your own selfish desires? Tis foolish, really. I can take any one of you and mold you into my servants, just as easily as I have him. And I can crush you even quicker, which I hestitate not to should you insist on meddling in our affairs. I can even destroy your precious pawn. Don't you care about your puppet's well being? Then you will do as I command. Accept the terrible fate of your comrade. Or prepare to brave the fearsome consquences. <br><br>I grow tired of your attempts to foil my will, to take back your puppet.<br>You have been warned... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ulorellai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lorellai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#B30000>(8/5/01 11:33:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: He is mine.</span><hr size=1> This is Jyllianne, <br><br>Eat my shorts.<br><br>/rude<br><br>have a pleasant day <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bdraconisrampant.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kishi>Kishi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#B30000>(8/6/01 7:20:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The search for Gazunga</span><hr size=1> Isn't my sister an eloquent speaker?  I was going to reply to you myself but I don't believe that there is anything I could say which would improve upon her previous comment.  I second her opinion and stand behind it completely.<br><br>Kishi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bdraconisrampant.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lashoon>Lashoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#B30000>(8/6/01 11:05:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The search for Gazunga</span><hr size=1> Dear Voice In My Head,<br><br>Take a good long look while you're in my skull. Look way in the back...you'll find my raging pit of hate I hold for orcs, goblins...those who hurt the innocent. See how it smolders? See how it consumes all that would do evil? See the storms of Karana that rage there? Take a good long look.<br><br>Hurt Gazunga in anyway, shape or form and you'll find that maelstrom unleashed on you. I probably won't be able to kill you, but you'll wish I had.<br><br>Go back to poking around my skull. Enjoy. Just stay away from those lewd thoughts of Kishi.<br><br><br>Lashoon Thunderbringer<br><br>He-Who-Makes-You-Regret-Messing-With-Gaz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bdraconisrampant.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kev>Kev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#B30000>(8/6/01 6:56:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hey Voice...SOD OFF!</span><hr size=1> Hey pal--<br><br>When ya;ve been around the Omniverse as many times as I have, then ya learn somethin very useful...idle threats from a coward to scared to even name himself are just that...idle threats.<br><br>We will come for Gazunga, and we will save him, and there aint a bloody thing you can do about it.<br><br>Kevin Worthington<br>Unique Traveller, whose helped kick more arse than you could even dream up<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> The Faceless One</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#B30000>(8/6/01 11:25:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I WARNED YOU!</span><hr size=1> I WARNED YOU! I told you to STAY BACK! But you keep pushing and pushing your luck, and you pay now!<br><br>Just ask your precious Kishi how the claws of Fear feel when plunged deep into her chest! And how terrible she must feel now! For her actions, her foolish attempts to save your dearest puppet, Gazunga, have backfired! LOL! I have torn him from the plane of mortals because of your insubordination! How does it feel, to know that he lies helpless now, imprisoned in my realm, suffering in terror unlike you will ever imagine!?<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Adiwen Silverlake Intrepid Spirits</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#B30000>(8/7/01 12:32:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> To the Leader of the Draconis Rampant Guild, Kurgn Thex</span><hr size=1> To Kurgn Thex, the Leader of the Draconis Rampant guild, and Lashoon Thunderbringer, noble Wizard of Draconis Rampant, do I, Adiwen SilverLake of the Intrepid Spirits guild, send greetings.  Hail and well met fellow travellers!<br><br>I write to you concerning a member of your guild, an Enchantress who goes by the name of Kishi.  I have previously hunted with her in the Crystal Caverns during a time when the Orc Population seemed to be unusually active.  Kishi herself left the caverns quite abruptly some time ago, but I thought little of it at the time, for this is common among those who adventure in these dark halls.  I remained to assist in weeding out the remnants of the ever present Ry'gorr, eventually succeeding in trimming them down to their prior population.<br><br>Leaving the caverns myself some time later, I went to make my way across the Eastern Wastes to my next destination.   After several days of travel I spotted a patch of blue which seemed to be unusual against the white that surrounded it.  Imagine my surprise when, upon investigating, it turned out to be the body of this enchantress, half buried in the snow.  I broke the ice away from her form and found that she was not dead; it was the corner of her robe, flapping, that had attracted my attention, and its warmth had kept her from the Dark Journey.<br><br>At the time of this writing, she remains in the land of the living; nevertheless I have gotten no story out of her, for she is delirious, in the grip of some strange affliction with which I am unfamiliar.  I have healed many a weakened traveller and it is my opinion that this strange illness has resulted from a magical duel or battle, yet does not seem to be the direct result of a spell.  It is almost as if a piece of her soul is missing or has been taken from her somehow, or she has cast it into some great void.  For all my skill I know little of the ways of the Enchanters, for these are the ways of mind and not body; I can take no other guess than that her affliction is something unique to the class of Enchanters.<br><br>I realize that this is disheartening news but wish to assure you that she is safe and well cared for.  As the closest thing to civilization, from the place she fell, was the Dwarven Stronghold of Frostone, I have taken the liberty of transporting her there.  She grows stronger daily and I feel certain that she shall regain her senses presently.  I have taken the liberty of writing to you, for I knew your name, Kurgn, from prior conversations with her, and in the past I have hunted with Lashoon Thunderbringer.  I shall be glad to speak with any representative you care to send, and shall write again when the Enchantress has recovered.  Better yet, with luck she shall write to you herself.  <br><br>In the meantime I remain,<br>Your Humble Servant,<br>Adiwen Silverlake<br>Intrepid Spirits<br><br><br>(OOC: The author of this letter is REALLY Kishi, who has used Adiwen's name with the gracious permission of his player.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bdraconisrampant.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lashoon>Lashoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#B30000>(8/7/01 6:53:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To the Leader of the Draconis Rampant Guild, Kurgn Thex</span><hr size=1> Adiwen,<br><br>Thank you for all your help. I owe you all for the service you have done for me and our guild. Somehow I will repay you.<br><br>I shall make my way to Frostone with winged feet. I will attend to Kishi until she is well again. Once that time comes, I will have need of you. Prepare yourself, war brother. Gird yourself. My anger has been roused. My wrath is great. Karana's storms brew. Vengeance is mine and it shall be terrible indeed.<br><br>Lashoon Thunderbringer<br>Wizard of 30 Arcane Circles<br>Bolt of Karana's Tempest <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ukeskan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keskan</