 class=m><span class=title> Handfast</span><hr size=1> (A couple of OOC notes here: This is what happened when Lashoon came to Kishi after the (lost) fight for Gazunga.  Lashoon was supposed to post it but he is having technical difficulties and has asked me to post it in his stead.  Enjoy!<br><br>Kishi<br>Enchanter of 35 Circles<br>Draconis Rampant))<br>--------------------------------------------------------<br><br>When Lashoon arrived in Frostone, Kishi was in the tiny room where she had been housed for some time. She looked bad; etherially pale, almost transparent. Her skin was cool and yet there was an expression of terrible suffering on her face. Her lips parted, mumbling. Lashoon could catch phrases; &quot;Lashoon,&quot; &quot;Gazunga,&quot; and quite often, &quot;Cazic has more than one face - Cazic has more than one face-&quot; Her hands were bound to the bedposts, with soft gentle cloth. <br><br>The reason why was clear almost immediately, as she tried to thrash mindlessly for a while, her cries of &quot;Cazic has more than one face&quot; becoming more shrill before devolving into random phrases. &quot;Plane - Cazic - Gazunga - won't leave you - no - NO! - Cazic - Lashoon - planes - musn't go...&quot; Finally she stilled, and once again her words were mere mumblings. <br><br>Lashoon heard the scream, knew it to be Kishi's, and ran towards it. The door that stood between him and the scream was knocked from its hinges with his casting of Thunderstrike. The Coldain guards came running, but backed away when they caught the look in Lashoon's eyes. The wizard entered the room and his jaw dropped. His love, Kishi, was pale as snow. Her eyes fluttered as she screamed and her body jerked against the restraints. Her hair was a tangled mess. Kishi's eyes were dark and sunken. With a sob he knelt and scooped her up in his arms. He pulled the high elf close despite her flailing. Tears streamed down his cheeks. He placed his mouth next to her ear and whispered softly. &quot;Shush now, be calm...Lashoon is here.&quot; <br><br>&quot;Lashoon,&quot; Kishi's voice was incoherent. &quot;Cazic has more than one face... Gazunga... Lashoon... please... Cazic... face... planes...&quot; But slowly her body began to relax, feeling his arms. Her struggles lessened, her head rested quietly on his shoulder, and her cries trailed away to vague mumblings. <br><br><br><br>Lashoon still cradled Kishi in his arms even though she had been asleep for hours. His arms were sore and tired, but he would not loosen the embrace. He placed his ear to her chest to listen to the beating heart within. Still strong, still fighting he thought. <br><br>The wizard did not pray often. He worshiped his god in other ways. He closed his eyes and sought his deity's attention. &quot;Karana, Lord of Storms, hear my plea. I am lost. I need your guidance and protection. I am no cleric or holy man, but I am your follower. I rejoice at your rain that brings life and stand in awe of the power of your tempests. I will follow you all my days. Help me now, mighty Karana. Guide me!&quot; <br><br>As he spoke the last words of his prayer the vision struck like a bolt. He was floating in a nowhere place...naked, alone. Darkness engulfed him. He peered through the inky blackness to make out a form coming towards him. Frail, white...Kishi, naked as well. He could see through her, see her soul, or what was left of it. It was jagged in place, melted in others. It feebly tried to reform itself but lacked the power. She would die without a renewed essence, of that he was sure. <br><br>The wizard reached for her, locked hands with her, and sent his spirit flowing into the enchanter's broken soul. Their eyes met, they connected, joined...became one. Their souls combined. A dark shadow rose to devour them, but the union of two hearts, two minds, two souls kept it at bay. It shrank back, leaving a vow to return to hanging within the limbo. Lashoon snapped awake suddenly. &quot;Thank you, Lord Karana! You have shown me the way. Thank you!!&quot; Lashoon closed his eyes and tried to remember all he knew of HandFasting. <br><br><br><br>It might have been hours later, or only minutes: but there was a stirring in his arms, the soft brush of long dark lashes against his skin, raising slowly, flicking softly in sleepy blinks. And then a voice, one that was soft and confused, weak... and yet familiar, bearing no trace of delirium. &quot;...Lashoon....?&quot; <br><br>Lashoon smiled weakly as his love awoke. He was spent, tired on all levels. Kishi noticed his state, saw the few new gray hairs poking through his dark ones. He was shaky in his movements. Concern, if not strength, rose in her. &quot;Lashoon...?  What have you done? What has happened to you?&quot; <br><br>The wizard calmly took her hands in his and smiled again, now with more vigor. &quot;We HandFasted, you and I. A piece of my soul is in you now and your's in mine.&quot; <br><br>&quot;But...you look so worn...&quot; <br><br>Lashoon nodded gently. &quot;It was taxing without your conscious effort. I had to put more of myself and more of my soul into it. More then normal. It was the only way to heal your spirit. We are forever joined.&quot; <br><br>Kishi smiled. &quot;Mmmm,&quot; she murmered as her head again drifted to Lashoons shoulder. &quot;Like that idea...&quot; Her voice was drained and her eyes were flickering closed in spite of herself. &quot;We can go... Cazic together... have to go.... right away.... soon as I put on my shoes... feels so nice... joined with you... so nice... happy... so...&quot; But the last few words were lost as her eyes closed, and she dropped off to sleep at once, a deep and healing sleep, resting her head on the shoulder of the man she loved. <br><br>Lashoon watched Kishi for a moment, closed his eyes, and was fast asleep. <br><br>The god Karana viewed the the two lovers closely. Karana, the Stormmaker, Keeper of Rains settled back into his throne of lightning. He was a god of neutrality, neither good nor evil. His storms caused growth just as surely as Tunare and destroyed the same as Cazic-Thule. His rains fell on the just and the unjust alike. Why then did he help this lone follower of his? Why did he risk angering the less impartial gods? The Faceless was a terrible enemy to make. Why then risk Cazic's wrath? <br><br>Karana smiled to himself. Why? Because he liked this wizard, this Thunderbringer. This Lashoon was so like himself. A summer shower to those he loves, a monsoon to those who cross him. A wonderful contradiction of passionate emotions, this human man. Karana liked that. Perhaps I might have use for this one he thought. Perhaps indeed. <br><br> <p><IMG SRC="http://www.draconisrampant.org/images/Characters/kishi_sig2.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bdraconisrampant.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lashoon>Lashoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#B30000>(8/9/01 8:28:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OOC Handfast</span><hr size=1> OOC:<br><br>Just as a note, HandFasting is the elvish ritual of joining of soul between lifemates. It is not something lightly taken. No couples ever seperate after HandFasting, except by death, and often their souls linger with their mate. It is for elves only. You might ask how Lashoon was able to do it. Well, he has elven blood in him, his mother a half-elf. Hopefully this clears up any confusion.<br><br>Lashoon's Player Tom <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdra